the plaintiffs point to the fact that they succeeded in establishing the issues that the company was insolvent, that there were reasonable grounds to suspect insolvency and that the defendant was aware of those reasonable grounds.
pursuant to s 1317s(2) of the act, the defendant be relieved wholly from any liability to pay to the plaintiffs, pursuant to s 588m of the act, any amount in respect of the loss and damage suffered by creditors of the company referred to in the schedule to the amended statement of claim herein, a copy of which schedule is annexed as schedule a to this order.
they also established that a reasonable person in a like position to the defendant would have been so aware of those reasonable grounds, and they succeeded in relation to the defences available under s 588h(2), which were not made out.